Background

		Mr. Dag J. Skattum serves as the Chief Executive Officer of Abingdon Capital Management LLC. Mr. Skattum served as a Managing Director and Head of London Office at One Thousand and One Voices, LLC from 2013 to 2014. He held various roles, including head of North American M&A and European M&A at J.P.Morgan from 1986 to 2007. He was employed Consulting business of Abingdon Partners LLC from 2013 to 2014. Mr. Skattum was a Partner of TPG Capital, L.P. for a span of six ... years from 2007 to 2013. He joined JPMorgan in 1986 and was employed for 21 years and served as its Co-Head of Global Mergers and Acquisitions from May 4, 2006 to July 2007 and also served as its Managing Director and Member of Mergers and Acquisitions Group. Mr. Skattum has more than 27 years of experience across private equity and strategic advisory. He has the experience in advising entrepreneurs building businesses across Sub-Saharan Africa and has covered the consumer/retail, healthcare, financial services and industrials sectors. He has been President of the Allegheny College since 2000. He serves as Co-chair capital campaign at Allegheny College. He has been Trusted advisor to Chief Executive Officer and Founder (on going) since 2011 He has been Vice-Chairman of J.P.Morgan Limited since January 2015. He has been Vice Chairman of the Board of Directors at Myelona Institute, Little Tock, Arkansas since 2012. He has been Independent Non-Executive Director of Sonae SGPS SA since December 16, 2015. He has been an Independent Director of Nabors Industries Ltd. since June 4, 2014. He has been a Member of the Board of Directors (Toronto, Canada HQ), the UK and the US at Right to Play since 2011. He serves as a Director of cancer institute (on going). Mr. Skattum serves on the Advisory Board of the UAMS Myeloma Institute for Research and Therapy, Little Rock, Arkansas; and the Board of Trustees of Allegheny College. Mr. Skattum received a B.A. in History from Allegheny College in 1984 and an MBA from the Simon Graduate School of Business at the University of Rochester in 1986. He attended Gjovik, Norway, High School, Science in 1980.Read Full Background




